Parliament, Monday, 3 December 2018 – The Ad Hoc Committee to inquire into the Intervention in the North West Provincial Government, in terms of Section 100 of the Constitution, will tomorrow be briefed by the Inter-Ministerial Task Team (IMTT) on an updated progress report since its last briefing on the intervention, which was received on 16 August 2018. Details of meeting: Date: Tuesday, 04 December 2018
	Time: 09:00-14:00
	Venue: Committee Room V475, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building, ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE AD HOC COMMITTEE TO INQUIRE INTO THE INTERVENTION IN THE NORTH WEST PROVINCIAL GOVERNMENT, MR CHAREL DE BEER. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8062
	Cell: 081 377 0686
